HEADWORD: Dispunct
<hw>Dis*punct"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Wanting in
punctilious respect; discourteous.</def> <mark>[Obs.]</mark>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>That were <qex>dispunct</qex> to the ladies.</q> <rj><qau>B.
